-- Amla, Clarke Are Shortlisted for ICC Cricketer of the Year Award
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2012-08-30T05:44:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-30/amla-clarke-are-shortlisted-for-icc-cricketer-of-the-year-award.html
Hashim Amla and Vernon Philander of
South Africa, Australia captain  Michael Clarke  and Sri Lanka
batsman  Kumar Sangakkara  were shortlisted for the International
Cricket Council’s Cricketer of the Year award.  The four players also made the final cut for the Test
Cricketer of the Year honor, while Sangakkara also is in
contention for the one-day award alongside teammate Lasith Malinga and India’s MS Dhoni and Virat Kohli.  The players were chosen by a 32-member panel based on their
performances between Aug. 4, 2011 and Aug. 6, 2012, the Dubai-
based  ICC said . The winners will be announced Sept. 15 in
Colombo, Sri Lanka.  Cricketer of the Year: Hashim Amla, Michael Clarke, Vernon
Philander, Kumar Sangakkara.  Test Cricketer of the Year: Hashim Amla, Michael Clarke 
Vernon Philander, Kumar Sangakkara.  One-Day International Cricketer of the Year: MS Dhoni,  Virat
Kohli , Lasith Malinga, Kumar Sangakkara.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  